msgid "Load Balancing External Components in Cluster Mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/External_Component_Configuration/Load_Balancing.rst:4
msgid ""
"This document describes how to load balance any external components using"
" Tigase XMPP Server and how to make Tigase’s components work as external "
"components in a cluster mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/External_Component_Configuration/Load_Balancing.rst:6
msgid ""
"*Please note, all configuration options described here apply to Tigase "
"XMPP Server version 8.0.0 or later.*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/External_Component_Configuration/Load_Balancing.rst:8
msgid "These are actually 2 separate topics:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/External_Component_Configuration/Load_Balancing.rst:10
msgid ""
"One is to distribute load over many instances of a single component to "
"handle larger traffic, or perhaps for high availability."
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/External_Component_Configuration/Load_Balancing.rst:12
msgid ""
"The second is to make Tigase’s components work as an external component "
"and make it work in a cluster mode, even if the component itself does not"
" support cluster mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../Tigase_Admistration/Components/External_Component_Configuration/Load_Balancing.rst:14
msgid ""
"Here are step by step instructions and configuration examples teaching "
"how to achieve both goals."
msgstr ""

